## SCI Eval vs Library -- Key Naming Differences

In `--eval` / daemon mode, functions live in `spel/` with **different names** than the library:

| You want to... | Library (Clojure) | SCI (`--eval` / daemon) |
|---|---|---|
| Navigate to URL | `(page/navigate pg url)` | `(spel/navigate url)` |
| Go back | `(page/go-back pg)` | `(spel/back)` |
| Go forward | `(page/go-forward pg)` | `(spel/forward)` |
| Reload | `(page/reload pg)` | `(spel/reload!)` |
| Get page title | `(page/title pg)` | `(spel/title)` |
| Get page URL | `(page/url pg)` | `(spel/url)` |
| Get page HTML | `(page/content pg)` | `(spel/html)` |
| Evaluate JS | `(page/evaluate pg expr)` | `(spel/eval-js expr)` |
| Wait for load | `(page/wait-for-load-state pg :state)` | `(spel/wait-for-load :state)` |
| Wait for selector | `(page/wait-for-selector pg sel)` | `(spel/wait-for sel)` |
| Wait for URL | `(page/wait-for-url pg url)` | `(spel/wait-for-url url)` |
| Sleep | `(page/wait-for-timeout pg ms)` | `(spel/sleep ms)` |
| CSS selector | `(page/locator pg sel)` | `(spel/$ sel)` |
| Multiple matches | — | `(spel/$$ sel)` |
| By text | `(page/get-by-text pg text)` | `(spel/$text text)` |
| By role | `(page/get-by-role pg role)` | `(spel/$role role)` |
| By label | `(page/get-by-label pg text)` | `(spel/$label text)` |
| By placeholder | `(page/get-by-placeholder pg text)` | `(spel/$placeholder text)` |
| By test ID | `(page/get-by-test-id pg id)` | `(spel/$test-id id)` |
| By alt text | `(page/get-by-alt-text pg text)` | `(spel/$alt-text text)` |
| By title attr | `(page/get-by-title pg text)` | `(spel/$title-attr text)` |
| Get text content | `(locator/text-content loc)` | `(spel/text loc)` |
| Get inner text | `(locator/inner-text loc)` | `(spel/inner-text loc)` |
| Get inner HTML | `(locator/inner-html loc)` | `(spel/inner-html loc)` |
| Get attribute | `(locator/get-attribute loc name)` | `(spel/attr loc name)` |
| Get input value | `(locator/input-value loc)` | `(spel/value loc)` |
| Count elements | `(locator/count-elements loc)` | `(spel/count-of loc)` |
| Bounding box | `(locator/bounding-box loc)` | `(spel/bbox loc)` |
| Is visible? | `(locator/is-visible? loc)` | `(spel/visible? loc)` |
| Is hidden? | `(locator/is-hidden? loc)` | `(spel/hidden? loc)` |
| Is enabled? | `(locator/is-enabled? loc)` | `(spel/enabled? loc)` |
| Is disabled? | `(locator/is-disabled? loc)` | `(spel/disabled? loc)` |
| Is editable? | `(locator/is-editable? loc)` | `(spel/editable? loc)` |
| Is checked? | `(locator/is-checked? loc)` | `(spel/checked? loc)` |
| Click | `(locator/click loc)` | `(spel/click loc)` |
| Fill | `(locator/fill loc text)` | `(spel/fill loc text)` |
| Select option | `(locator/select-option loc val)` | `(spel/select loc val)` |
| First element | `(locator/first-element loc)` | `(spel/first loc)` |
| Last element | `(locator/last-element loc)` | `(spel/last loc)` |
| Nth element | `(locator/nth-element loc n)` | `(spel/nth loc n)` |
| Take screenshot | `(page/screenshot pg opts)` | `(spel/screenshot opts)` |
| Generate PDF | `(page/pdf pg opts)` | `(spel/pdf opts)` |
| Set viewport | `(page/set-viewport-size pg w h)` | `(spel/set-viewport-size! w h)` |
| Emulate media | `(page/emulate-media! pg opts)` | `(spel/emulate-media! opts)` |

**Key difference**: Library takes explicit `page`/`locator`. Eval uses the implicit daemon page.

## Top 10 Patterns (80% of Use Cases)

### 1. Screenshot

```bash
# CLI
spel open https://example.com --screenshot /tmp/shot.png

# --eval: full page screenshot
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://en.wikipedia.org")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(spel/screenshot {:path "/tmp/full.png" :full-page true})
'
```

Library:
```clojure
(core/with-testing-page [pg]
  (page/navigate pg "https://example.com")
  (page/screenshot pg {:path "/tmp/shot.png"}))
```

### 2. Navigate and Wait

```bash
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://example.com")
(spel/wait-for-load)                     ;; default: :load state
(spel/wait-for-load :networkidle)        ;; wait for no network activity
(println (spel/title))
'
```

**Wait states**: `:load` (default), `:domcontentloaded`, `:networkidle`. (`:commit` is navigation-only via `{:wait-until :commit}`, not valid for `wait-for-load`.)

### 3. Click, Fill, and Interact

```bash
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://example.com/login")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(spel/fill "#username" "john@example.com")
(spel/fill "#password" "secret123")
(spel/click "button[type=submit]")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(println "Logged in:" (spel/title))
'
```

Selectors accept CSS, snapshot refs (`"e1"` or `"@e1"`), or Locator objects.

### 4. Accessibility Snapshot (See the Page Like an Agent)

```bash
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://news.ycombinator.com")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(let [snap (spel/snapshot)]
  ;; snap = {:tree "..." :refs [...] :counter N}
  (println (:tree snap))          ;; human-readable accessibility tree
  (println "Refs:" (count (:refs snap))))
;; Click by ref ID from snapshot:
(spel/click "e1")
'
```

Or via CLI: `spel snapshot` (text), `spel snapshot --json` (machine-readable).

### 5. Annotated Screenshot

```bash
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://onet.pl")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(let [snap (spel/snapshot)
      refs (:refs snap)]
  (spel/save-annotated-screenshot! refs "/tmp/annotated.png"))
'
```

Or via CLI: `spel annotate /tmp/annotated.png`

### 6. Assertions

```bash
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://example.com")
(spel/wait-for-load)

;; Page-level
(spel/assert-title "Example Domain")
(spel/assert-url "https://example.com/")      ;; exact match only

;; Element-level
(spel/assert-visible "h1")
(spel/assert-contains-text "h1" "Example")
(spel/assert-text "h1" "Example Domain")
(spel/assert-hidden "#nonexistent")

;; Negation
(let [neg (spel/assert-not "h1")]
  (assert/is-hidden neg))                      ;; would FAIL (h1 is visible)

(println "All assertions passed!")
'
```

**Important**: `assert-url` does exact string match only. No regex/substring.

### 7. PDF Generation

```bash
# CLI
spel pdf /tmp/page.pdf

# --eval (Chromium headless only)
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clojure")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(spel/pdf {:path "/tmp/article.pdf" :format "A4"})
'
```

PDF options: `:format` ("A4", "Letter"), `:landscape`, `:margin`, `:print-background`. See @refs/PDF_STITCH_VIDEO.md.

### 8. Image Stitching

```bash
# CLI
spel stitch /tmp/top.png /tmp/bottom.png -o /tmp/stitched.png

# --eval: scroll-and-stitch workflow
spel --eval '
(spel/navigate "https://news.ycombinator.com")
(spel/wait-for-load)
(spel/screenshot {:path "/tmp/top.png"})
(spel/eval-js "window.scrollTo(0, 500)")
(spel/sleep 500)
(spel/screenshot {:path "/tmp/bottom.png"})
(let [i1 (stitch/read-image "/tmp/top.png")
      i2 (stitch/read-image "/tmp/bottom.png")]
  (stitch/stitch-vertical [i1 i2] "/tmp/stitched.png"))
'
```

### 9. Write a Full Test with Allure Reporting

```clojure
(ns {{ns}}.e2e-test
  (:require
   [com.blockether.spel.page :as page]
   [com.blockether.spel.locator :as locator]
   [com.blockether.spel.test-fixtures :refer [*page* with-playwright with-browser with-page]]
   [com.blockether.spel.allure :refer [defdescribe describe expect it]]))

(defdescribe example-test
  (describe "example.com navigation"
    {:context [with-playwright with-browser with-page]}
    (it "has correct title"
      (page/navigate *page* "https://example.com")
      (expect (= "Example Domain" (page/title *page*))))
    (it "has a link to IANA"
      (let [link (page/get-by-text *page* "More information...")]
        (expect (locator/is-visible? link))))))
```

{{testing-conventions}}

