## SCI Eval Namespaces

| Namespace | Purpose | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `spel/` | Simplified API (implicit page) | `(spel/navigate url)` |
| `snapshot/` | Accessibility snapshots | `(snapshot/capture)` |
| `annotate/` | Screenshot annotations | `(annotate/save! refs path)` |
| `stitch/` | Image stitching | `(stitch/stitch-vertical imgs path)` |
| `input/` | Keyboard, mouse, touch | `(input/key-press kb "Enter")` |
| `frame/` | Frame/iframe ops | `(frame/navigate f url)` |
| `net/` | Network request/response | `(net/response-status resp)` |
| `loc/` | Raw locator operations | `(loc/click locator)` |
| `assert/` | Playwright assertions | `(assert/has-text la "text")` |
| `core/` | Lifecycle macros | `(core/with-page [pg ...])` |
| `page/` | Raw page operations | `(page/navigate pg url)` |
| `locator/` | Raw locator (alias of loc/) | `(locator/fill loc val)` |
| `role/` | AriaRole constants | `role/button`, `role/link` |
| `markdown/` | Markdown table parsing | `(markdown/from-markdown-table s)` |

Also available: `clojure.core`, `clojure.string`, `clojure.set`, `clojure.edn`, `clojure.java.io` (as `io`), `slurp`, `spit`, Java interop on Playwright classes. See @refs/EVAL_GUIDE.md for full details.

## Selector Types

Every `spel/` function taking a `sel` argument accepts:

| Type | Example | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| CSS selector | `"#id"`, `".class"`, `"button"` | Standard CSS |
| Snapshot ref | `"e1"` or `"@e1"` | From `(spel/snapshot)` refs |
| Locator object | `(spel/$ "div")` | Pass-through |
| Text selector | Via `(spel/$text "Click me")` | Returns Locator |
| Role selector | Via `(spel/$role role/button)` | Returns Locator |
| Label selector | Via `(spel/$label "Email")` | Returns Locator |

## Error Handling

Library functions return anomaly maps instead of throwing:

```clojure
(let [result (page/navigate pg "https://example.com")]
  (if (core/anomaly? result)
    (println "Error:" (:cognitect.anomalies/message result))
    (println "OK")))
```

| Playwright Exception | Anomaly Category |
|---|---|
| `TimeoutError` | `:cognitect.anomalies/busy` |
| `TargetClosedError` | `:cognitect.anomalies/interrupted` |
| `PlaywrightException` | `:cognitect.anomalies/fault` |

In `--eval` / daemon mode, errors throw by default for natural short-circuit behavior.

## Resource Lifecycle (Library)

Always use `with-*` macros for cleanup:

```clojure
;; Quick: all-in-one
(core/with-testing-page [pg]
  (page/navigate pg "https://example.com")
  (page/title pg))

;; With options
(core/with-testing-page {:device :iphone-14 :locale "fr-FR"} [pg]
  (page/navigate pg "https://example.com"))

;; Explicit nesting
(core/with-playwright [pw]
  (core/with-browser [browser (core/launch-chromium pw {:headless true})]
    (core/with-context [ctx (core/new-context browser)]
      (core/with-page [pg (core/new-page-from-context ctx)]
        (page/navigate pg "https://example.com")))))
```

| Option | Values | Default |
|---|---|---|
| `:browser-type` | `:chromium`, `:firefox`, `:webkit` | `:chromium` |
| `:headless` | `true`, `false` | `true` |
| `:device` | `:iphone-14`, `:pixel-7`, `:ipad` | -- |
| `:viewport` | `:mobile`, `:tablet`, `:desktop-hd`, `{:width N :height N}` | browser default |
| `:slow-mo` | Millis | -- |
| `:profile` | Path to user data dir | -- |
| `:locale` | `"en-US"`, `"fr-FR"` | -- |

